-- Nomura Updates Latin American Currency Forecasts for 2012
-- B y   S e b a s t i a n   B o y d
-- 2012-02-02T15:19:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-02/nomura-updates-latin-american-currency-forecasts-for-2012.html
Strategists at Nomura Securities Inc.
in  New York  updated forecasts for  Latin America , showing they
expect most regional currencies to close the year stronger, and
the Brazilian real to be weaker than previously forecast.  Nomura raised its year-end forecasts for the Chilean,
Colombian, Mexican and Argentine currencies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sebastian Boyd in Santiago at 
 sboyd9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  